  <activity xml:id="act-func-graphs">
    <title>Solving Functions Graphically</title>
    
    <statement>
      <p>
        In <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/>, you found many equations, most of them non-linear. Relationships between some of the data sets helped you determine other equations. What questions might we ask about the data sets that can be answered using the equations? Brainstorm with your group. Write at least 3 questions about <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/> that can be answered using one or more of the equations. Share your questions with the class.
      </p>
      <p>
        Questions that are frequently asked about Batty Functions include:
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              How many bats are in group 7? Group <m>n</m>?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              If a group has 37 bats, what is the group number? If a group has <m>b</m> bats, what is the group number?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              What is a reasonable domain for each function?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              What is a reasonable range for each function?
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        Did you ask questions like these? Look at the graphs you drew for <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/> How can a graph help you answer these questions? How can a table help? Choose some of the questions about <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/> that you and others wrote. Answer as many of them as you can in context. If you still have questions, write them down to ask once the <xref text="title" ref="act-batty-func"/> questions have been answered.
      </p>
      <p>
        Look at the graph in <xref ref="fig-parab-ball"/>. Suppose the graph represents the height, <m>h</m>, of a ball <m>t</m> seconds after it is thrown. Ask and answer similar questions as those above for this context and graph. Can you find the answer exactly in each case? Why or why not?
      </p>
      <figure xml:id="fig-parab-ball">
        <caption></caption>
        <image source="parab-ball" width="50%">
          <description></description>
        </image>
      </figure>
    </statement>
  </activity>

